OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,FThe Chief Justice has rejected claims
OL,7,Fthat perpetrators of domestic abuse
OL,8,Fare being let off lightly and insisted
OL,9,Fshe is committed to increasing the
OL,10,Fsentences available to them in the
OL,11,FMagistrates Court as well as trying
OL,12,Fthese crimes in the Crown Court where
OL,13,Ftougher tariffs can be imposed.
OL,15,FUTV revealed within its series on
OL,16,Fviolence against women and girls that
OL,17,Fthe latest figures from the department
OL,18,Fof justice show only a third of
OL,19,Fperpetrators of these types of crimes
OL,20,Fspent any time behind bars and only a
OL,21,Fminority were jailed for over a year.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/17
