OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,FDame Siobhan Keegan explained that
OL,7,Fwhile conviction rates have almost
OL,8,Fdoubled in the last five years the
OL,9,Freason there is a high percentage of
OL,10,Fnon-custodial sentences is because
OL,11,Fmost of these cases are prosecuted in
OL,12,Fthe Magistrates Court.
OL,14,F"The Magistrates Court has a statutory
OL,15,Flimit in terms of what can be imposed
OL,16,Fas a sentence, usually 12 months. And
OL,17,Fby law, half of that is spent on
OL,18,Flicense. So that's not down to judges.
OL,19,FThat's the law. So you can see the
OL,20,Fsentences of imprisonment are short,"
OL,21,Fshe said.
OL,26,@vD@AOU|D@eO]
