OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F449A1743013875
OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,F"The second thing is to bring some of
OL,7,Fthese cases to the higher court. So
OL,8,Fthat's the Crown Court and I have said
OL,9,Fthat in a number of cases recently
OL,10,Fthat particularly with persistent
OL,11,Fdomestic violence, prosecutors should
OL,12,Factively consider these cases going to
OL,13,Fthe Crown Court where the Crown Court
OL,14,Fjudge has the ability to impose a
OL,15,Fheftier sentence.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/17
