OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,F"But my own view is that the judiciary
OL,7,Fis well aware of the need to deter
OL,8,Fdomestic violence."
OL,10,FThe law has changed but Dame Siobhan
OL,11,FKeegan accepted the rate of violence
OL,12,Fagainst women and girls remains
OL,13,Fstubbornly high.
OL,15,FEight women were killed in violent
OL,16,Fcircumstances in Northern Ireland in
OL,17,F2024.
OL,19,F30,000 domestic abuse incidents were
OL,20,Frecorded and the vast majority of
OL,21,Fvictims were women.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/17
