OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,F"Well, I can't speak for perpetrators,
OL,7,Fbut I personally think if they see,
OL,8,Fparticularly in the Court of Appeal,
OL,9,Fwhich has spoken on this, they should
OL,10,Fknow that this is treated really
OL,11,Fseriously.
OL,13,F"Sentences are going to reflect this.
OL,14,FAnd as I've said, cases should be
OL,15,Fbrought to the Crown Court for
OL,16,Fpersistent domestic abuse and higher
OL,17,Fsentences imposed. So I'd be surprised
OL,18,Fif they thought that they're going to
OL,19,Fget an easy ride, because that is not
OL,20,Fthe case," she said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU|D@JO]
