OL,3,CNI's top judge: Domestic abusers
OL,4,Caren't being let off lightly
OL,6,FWhen asked about certain judges'
OL,7,Fcomments in cases involving domestic
OL,8,Fabuse and whether their gender has had
OL,9,Fany bearing on how they deal with
OL,10,Fthese types of crimes, Dame Keegan
OL,11,Fsaid she was committed to training all
OL,12,Fjudges irrespective of sex.
OL,14,F"The judiciary is happily going to a
OL,15,Fplace that is not so male dominated as
OL,16,Fit used to be.
OL,18,F"But to be honest, I'm not sure that I
OL,19,Fwould criticise my male colleagues,
OL,20,Fparticularly in this area.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/17
